## Edge Cases Mitigated

| # | Edge Case | Mitigation | Code Location |
|---|-----------|------------|---------------|
| 1 | Tool not installed | `_check_tools()` at startup + `_resolve_tool()` per-task returns `TOOL_MISSING` | `worker.py:_check_tools`, `tasks.py:_resolve_tool` |
| 2 | Tool version mismatch | `_get_tool_version()` captures version string; logged in result's `tool_version` field | `tasks.py:_get_tool_version` |
| 3 | Output too large (>50MB) | Size guard in `_run_subprocess()` raises `MemoryError` | `tasks.py:_run_subprocess` |
| 4 | Malformed JSON line | `BaseParser.parse()` catches per-line exceptions, logs warning, continues | `parsers.py:BaseParser.parse` |
| 5 | Invalid target domain | `_validate_target()` regex allowlist blocks shell metacharacters | `tasks.py:_validate_target` |
| 6 | Network unreachable | Tool times out вҶ’ subprocess timeout вҶ’ `TIMEOUT` error | `tasks.py:_run_subprocess` |
| 7 | Worker OOM (RAM >90%) | `_resource_monitor_loop()` pauses task acceptance via `_ram_ok` event | `worker.py:_resource_monitor_loop` |
| 8 | Redis connection lost | `_ensure_redis()` reconnects with exponential backoff; results buffered in-memory | `worker.py:_ensure_redis`, `_push_result` |
| 9 | Duplicate task | Worker processes idempotently; dedup is orchestrator's responsibility but task_id tracking helps | `worker.py:_process_one` |
| 10 | Missing params | `merged_params = {**default_params, **task.params}` fills from config defaults | `worker.py:_execute_task` |
| 11 | Subprocess hangs | `communicate(timeout=N)` + `killpg(SIGKILL)` ensures no zombie | `tasks.py:_run_subprocess` |
| 12 | Multiple workers on same host | `worker_id = "recon-{hostname}-{PID}"` guarantees uniqueness | `worker.py:_load_config` |
| 13 | Graceful shutdown | SIGTERM/SIGINT caught; `_shutdown_event` lets current task finish | `worker.py:_handle_signal` |
| 14 | Empty tool output | Parser detects and returns `count: 0` with warning | `parsers.py:BaseParser.parse` |
| 15 | Invalid JSON task payload | Caught in `_process_one`, returns FAILED result | `worker.py:_process_one` |
| 16 | Unknown task type | `TASK_DISPATCH.get()` returns None вҶ’ FAILED with UNKNOWN error | `worker.py:_execute_task` |
| 17 | Result buffer overflow | Hard limit (`result_buffer_limit`); excess results are dropped with ERROR log | `worker.py:_push_result` |
| 18 | Shell injection via params | All params validated/sanitised; `shell=False` in Popen | `tasks.py` throughout |
| 19 | Config file missing | `FileNotFoundError` raised explicitly with searched paths listed | `worker.py:_load_config` |
| 20 | Nuclei non-zero exit on "no results" | Special-cased: treated as success with empty findings | `tasks.py:nuclei_task` |

