## Remaining Loopholes & Future Improvements

| Priority | Gap | Improvement |
|----------|-----|-------------|
| рҹ”ҙ High | No streaming output size guard during execution | Implement line-by-line streaming with byte counter; kill process mid-stream if threshold exceeded (currently only post-mortem check) |
| рҹ”ҙ High | No mTLS for Redis | Use `redis.Redis(ssl=True, ssl_certfile=..., ssl_keyfile=...)` in production |
| рҹҹЎ Medium | No task deduplication at worker level | Add bloom filter or Redis `SISMEMBER` check before execution |
| рҹҹЎ Medium | No rate limiting between tasks | Add configurable delay between task completions to prevent resource spike |
| рҹҹЎ Medium | Single-threaded execution | Consider `asyncio` or worker pool for parallel task execution (with resource bounds) |
| рҹҹЎ Medium | No Prometheus/OpenTelemetry metrics | Add `prometheus_client` counters for tasks_processed, errors, latency histograms |
| рҹҹў Low | Tool auto-installation | Auto-download missing tools via `go install` on first run |
| рҹҹў Low | No task priority queue | Support multiple priority queues (e.g., `queue:recon:critical`, `queue:recon:normal`) |
| рҹҹў Low | Config hot-reload | Watch config file for changes and reload without restart |
| рҹҹў Low | Result compression | gzip large results before pushing to Redis |

